OL,4,G````````````BSECONDARYG``````Su;/!G    
OL,5,ECHRISTMASGby James, 13, Garth Hill     
OL,6,GSchool, Bracknell                      
OL,7,BChildren dreaming of boxes of fun,     
OL,8,BHoping to hear Santa come,             
OL,9,BRush to open presents under the tree   
OL,10,BIllusions fulfilled, well some maybe.  
OL,11,BSo much paper, torn and tattered,      
OL,12,BTurkey dinner and parents shattered.   
OL,13,BMistletoe kisses from family & friends,
OL,14,BAll too soon the magic will end.       
OL,15,BAll that's left is best wishes to send.
OL,16,BWhen a child has a Christmas not so,   
OL,17,BIt's because adults no care did show.  
OL,18,BSome even blindly look away.           
OL,19,BHave a care, is what I say.            
